Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Meanwhile in a hot skillet, brown the chicken in olive oil over high heat for approximately 5 minutes. Add onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, garlic and Cajun seasoning and saute for 3 additional minutes. Stir in wine then season with salt and pepper; reduce liquid by half. Add cream and bring to simmer. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions. Drain and toss with sauce and stir in cheese before serving.